SIMPLE: passe_partout
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Passe partout
<hw>Passe" par`tout"</hw></mhw>
<pr>(p⟦aum⟧s` p⟦aum⟧r`t⟦oomac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from
<ets>passer</ets> to pass + <ets>partout</ets> everywhere.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>That by which one can pass anywhere; a
safe-conduct.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A master key; a latchkey.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A light picture frame or mat of cardboard, wood, or
the like, usually put between the picture and the glass, and sometimes
serving for several pictures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A strip of adhesive paper or gummed tape used to
mount a picture between a piece of glass and a backing.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The method of mounting a picture between a piece of
glass and a backing, using a passe-partout{4}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passer</ent>⟦br⟧
